    90	class RMSNorm(CustomOp):
    91	    """Root mean square normalization.
    92	
    93	    Computes x -> w * x / sqrt(E[x^2] + eps) where w is the learned weight.
    94	    Refer to https://arxiv.org/abs/1910.07467
    95	    """
    96	
    97	    def __init__(
    98	        self,
    99	        hidden_size: int,
   100	        eps: float = 1e-6,
   101	        var_hidden_size: Optional[int] = None,
   102	        has_weight: bool = True,
   103	        dtype: Optional[torch.dtype] = None,
   104	    ) -> None:
   105	        super().__init__()
   106	
   107	        self.hidden_size = hidden_size
   108	        self.variance_epsilon = eps
   109	        self.variance_size_override = (None if var_hidden_size == hidden_size
   110	                                       else var_hidden_size)
   111	        self.has_weight = has_weight
   112	        if dtype is not None:
   113	            self.weight = torch.ones(hidden_size, dtype=dtype)
   114	        else:
   115	            self.weight = torch.ones(hidden_size)
   116	        if self.has_weight:
   117	            self.weight = nn.Parameter(self.weight)
   118	
   119	    def forward_native(
   120	        self,
   121	        x: torch.Tensor,
   122	        residual: Optional[torch.Tensor] = None,
   123	    ) -> Union[torch.Tensor, tuple[torch.Tensor, torch.Tensor]]:
   124	        """PyTorch-native implementation equivalent to forward()."""
   125	        orig_dtype = x.dtype
   126	        x = x.to(torch.float32)
   127	        if residual is not None:
   128	            x = x + residual.to(torch.float32)
   129	            residual = x.to(orig_dtype)
   130	
   131	        hidden_size = x.shape[-1]
   132	        if hidden_size != self.hidden_size:
   133	            raise ValueError("Expected hidden_size to be "
   134	                             f"{self.hidden_size}, but found: {hidden_size}")
   135	
   136	        if self.variance_size_override is None:
   137	            x_var = x
   138	        else:
   139	            if hidden_size < self.variance_size_override:
   140	                raise ValueError(
   141	                    "Expected hidden_size to be at least "
   142	                    f"{self.variance_size_override}, but found: {hidden_size}")
   143	
   144	            x_var = x[:, :, :self.variance_size_override]
   145	
   146	        variance = x_var.pow(2).mean(dim=-1, keepdim=True)
   147	
   148	        x = x * torch.rsqrt(variance + self.variance_epsilon)
   149	        x = x.to(orig_dtype)
   150	        if self.has_weight:
   151	            x = x * self.weight
   152	        if residual is None:
   153	            return x
   154	        else:
   155	            return x, residual

    """

    def pairwise(iterable):

        Can be removed when Python 3.9 support is dropped.
        """
        iterator = iter(iterable)

            a = b

    59	class NemotronHMLP(nn.Module):
    60	
    61	    def __init__(
    62	        self,
    63	        config: NemotronHConfig,
    64	        quant_config: Optional[QuantizationConfig] = None,
    65	        bias: bool = False,
    66	    ) -> None:
    67	        super().__init__()
    68	        self.up_proj = MergedColumnParallelLinear(
    69	            input_size=config.hidden_size,
    70	            output_sizes=[config.intermediate_size],
    71	            bias=bias,
    72	            quant_config=quant_config,
    73	        )
    74	        self.down_proj = RowParallelLinear(
    75	            input_size=config.intermediate_size,
    76	            output_size=config.hidden_size,
    77	            bias=bias,
    78	            quant_config=quant_config,
    79	        )
    80	        self.act_fn = ReLUSquaredActivation()
    81	
    82	    def forward(self, x: torch.Tensor):
    83	        x, _ = self.up_proj(x)
    84	        x = self.act_fn(x)
    85	        x, _ = self.down_proj(x)
    86	        return x

   172	class NemotronHAttention(nn.Module):
   173	
   174	    def __init__(
   175	        self,
   176	        config: NemotronHConfig,
   177	        layer_idx: int,
   178	        cache_config: Optional[CacheConfig] = None,
   179	        quant_config: Optional[QuantizationConfig] = None,
   180	        prefix: str = "",
   181	    ) -> None:
   182	        super().__init__()
   183	        self.hidden_size = config.hidden_size
   184	        tp_size = get_tensor_model_parallel_world_size()
   185	        self.total_num_heads = config.num_attention_heads
   186	        assert self.total_num_heads % tp_size == 0
   187	        self.num_heads = self.total_num_heads // tp_size
   188	        self.total_num_kv_heads = config.num_key_value_heads
   189	        if self.total_num_kv_heads >= tp_size:
   190	            # Number of KV heads is greater than TP size, so we partition
   191	            # the KV heads across multiple tensor parallel GPUs.
   192	            assert self.total_num_kv_heads % tp_size == 0
   193	        else:
   194	            # Number of KV heads is less than TP size, so we replicate
   195	            # the KV heads across multiple tensor parallel GPUs.
   196	            assert tp_size % self.total_num_kv_heads == 0
   197	        self.num_kv_heads = max(1, self.total_num_kv_heads // tp_size)
   198	        self.head_dim = config.hidden_size // self.total_num_heads
   199	        self.q_size = self.num_heads * self.head_dim
   200	        self.kv_size = self.num_kv_heads * self.head_dim
   201	        self.scaling = self.head_dim**-0.5
   202	
   203	        self.qkv_proj = QKVParallelLinear(
   204	            config.hidden_size,
   205	            self.head_dim,
   206	            self.total_num_heads,
   207	            self.total_num_kv_heads,
   208	            bias=False,
   209	            quant_config=quant_config,
   210	        )
   211	        self.o_proj = RowParallelLinear(
   212	            self.total_num_heads * self.head_dim,
   213	            config.hidden_size,
   214	            bias=False,
   215	            quant_config=quant_config,
   216	        )
   217	
   218	        self.attn = Attention(
   219	            self.num_heads,
   220	            self.head_dim,
   221	            self.scaling,
   222	            num_kv_heads=self.num_kv_heads,
   223	            cache_config=cache_config,
   224	            prefix=f"{prefix}.attn",
   225	        )
   226	
   227	    def forward(
   228	        self,
   229	        hidden_states: torch.Tensor,
   230	        **kwargs,
   231	    ) -> torch.Tensor:
   232	        qkv, _ = self.qkv_proj(hidden_states)
   233	        q, k, v = qkv.split([self.q_size, self.kv_size, self.kv_size], dim=-1)
   234	        attn_output = self.attn(q, k, v)
   235	        output, _ = self.o_proj(attn_output)
   236	        return output

   413	                                   if proj in name)

   415	                param = params_dict[name]

    91	    """Root mean square normalization.
    92	
    93	    Computes x -> w * x / sqrt(E[x^2] + eps) where w is the learned weight.
    94	    Refer to https://arxiv.org/abs/1910.07467
    95	    """
    96	
    97	    def __init__(

   106

   108	        self.variance_epsilon = eps
   109	        self.variance_size_override = (None if var_hidden_size == hidden_size
   110	                                       else var_hidden_size)
   111	        self.has_weight = has_weight
   112	        if dtype is not None:
   113	            self.weight = torch.ones(hidden_size, dtype=dtype)
   114	        else:
   115	            self.weight = torch.ones(hidden_size)
   116	        if self.has_weight:
   117	            self.weight = nn.Parameter(self.weight)
   118

   120	        self,
   121	        x: torch.Tensor,
   122	        residual: Optional[torch.Tensor] = None,
   123	    ) -> Union[torch.Tensor, tuple[torch.Tensor, torch.Tensor]]:
   124	        """PyTorch-native implementation equivalent to forward()."""
   125	        orig_dtype = x.dtype
   126	        x = x.to(torch.float32)
   127	        if residual is not None:
   128	            x = x + residual.to(torch.float32)
   129	            residual = x.to(orig_dtype)
   130	
   131	        hidden_size = x.shape[-1]
   132	        if hidden_size != self.hidden_size:
   133	            raise ValueError("Expected hidden_size to be "
   134	                             f"{self.hidden_size}, but found: {hidden_size}")
   135

   137	            x_var = x

   152	        if residual is None:

   218	class MambaMixer2(CustomOp):
   219	    """
   220	    Compute ∆, A, B, C, and D the state space parameters and compute
   221	    the `contextualized_states`. A, D are input independent
   222	    (see Mamba paper [1] Section 3.5.2 "Interpretation of A"
   223	    for why A isn't selective) ∆, B, C are input-dependent
   224	    (this is a key difference between Mamba and the linear time
   225	    invariant S4, and is why Mamba is called
   226	    **selective** state spaces)
   227	    """
   228	
   229	    def __init__(
   230	        self,
   231	        hidden_size: int,
   232	        ssm_state_size: int,
   233	        conv_kernel_size: int,
   234	        intermediate_size: int,
   235	        use_conv_bias: bool,
   236	        use_bias: bool,
   237	        n_groups: int = 1,
   238	        num_heads: int = 128,
   239	        head_dim: int = 64,
   240	        rms_norm_eps: float = 1e-5,
   241	        activation: str = "silu",
   242	        use_rms_norm: bool = True,
   243	        quant_config: Optional[QuantizationConfig] = None,
   244	    ):
   245	        super().__init__()
   246	
   247	        # For TP, the sharding plan is as follows:
   248	        # - for the conv modules, since
   249	        #   conv_dim = intermediate_size * 2 * n_groups * ssm_state_size,
   250	        #   we shard intermediate_size and n_groups
   251	        # - since intermediate_size = n_heads * head_dim, sharding on
   252	        #   intermediate_size is achieved by sharding on n_heads.
   253	        # - IF, world_size divides groups, then sharding
   254	        #   (n_groups / world_size, n_heads / world_size)
   255	        #   also maintains the invariant n_heads % n_groups == 0
   256	        # - HOWEVER IF, world_size DOES NOT divide groups, then we need
   257	        #   to allocate extra space in the shard, such that groups
   258	        #   may be replicated to follow the head shard.
   259	        # - NOTE: currently for the world size DOES NOT divide groups
   260	        #   case, we only support the case when n_groups == 1
   261	        self.tp_size = get_tensor_model_parallel_world_size()
   262	        tp_rank = get_tensor_model_parallel_rank()
   263	
   264	        assert (num_heads % self.tp_size == 0
   265	                ), "Tensor parallel world size must divide num heads."
   266	
   267	        assert (n_groups % self.tp_size) == 0 or n_groups == 1, (
   268	            "If tensor parallel world size does not divide num_heads, "
   269	            "then num_groups must equal 1.")
   270	
   271	        assert (
   272	            self.tp_size == 1 or quant_config is None
   273	        ), "Tensor parallel currently not supported for quantized models."
   274	
   275	        self.ssm_state_size = ssm_state_size
   276	        self.activation = activation
   277	
   278	        self.intermediate_size = intermediate_size
   279	        self.head_dim = head_dim
   280	        self.num_heads = num_heads
   281	
   282	        self.n_groups = n_groups
   283	        if n_groups % self.tp_size != 0:
   284	            # - for TP we shard conv_dim by sharding on n_groups,
   285	            # - but if n_groups cannot divide tp_size, we need to
   286	            #   extend some extra groups
   287	            self.n_groups = n_groups + extra_groups_for_head_shards(
   288	                n_groups, self.tp_size)
   289	
   290	        self.conv_dim = intermediate_size + 2 * self.n_groups * ssm_state_size
   291	        self.conv1d = ColumnParallelLinear(
   292	            input_size=conv_kernel_size,
   293	            output_size=self.conv_dim,
   294	            bias=use_conv_bias,
   295	            quant_config=None,
   296	        )
   297	        # unsqueeze to fit conv1d weights shape into the linear weights shape.
   298	        # Can't do this in `weight_loader` since it already exists in
